The mystery of the will in Norway is committed: The Russians tested a rocket
There has been a strange light phenomenon of unknown origin over Norway.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has recognized that yesterday have tested a rocket intercontinental ballistic missile near the Norwegian border.
The launch has been a failure and the missile "bulava" which was originally scheduled to be the pride of the Russian army is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir putin.
His presence repeated tests of the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights.
Most of the time, either Bulava has not disappeared, or it is damaged in flight.
Russian newspapers talk of "Bulava" as the "missile that not."
A missile that is not
This 13th test took place at the beginning.
It is only at the end of the flight that there was damage to appliance.
This is clearly the engine of the third floor of the rocket that exploded.
This time, "Bulava" of the nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij which was sailing under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile can be fired from a moving boat and
That is why the mysterious light above Norway caused by an unidentified flying object precisely was on a "bulava" flawed.
Moreover, the Norwegian did not doubt for a moment that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk of failure.
The first two stages of the rocket resisted and the damage was confined to the third.
In previous cases, the engines have been failures on the first floor.
Although none of the test launches went smoothly, the direction of the Ministry of Defence considers that only six out of thirteen were failures.
This success rate of almost fifty percent fills the general optimism and they therefore argue that a day "Bulava" fly without problems and that it will prevail even ten nuclei of hypersonic a total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
