Hyundai has listened to the unions and cancels all overtime.
The direction of the plant Hyundai of Nošovice has agreed with unions to cancel all overtime.
It is precisely because of overtime frequent that unions have declared a state of emergency strike Monday.
The spokesman Petr Vaněk factory Hyundai confirmed.
The management, however, wants to reach agreement with the unions on a Saturday worked again this year.
We cannot abandon our production plan, it is essential, that is why overtime volunteers have been proposed on Saturday, 19 December knowing that there would be two teams, said Vaněk.
The site Sedmička.cz indicated that the company has proposed a bonus CZK 400 employees who would be part of the team on Saturday.
It will also checking for the day worked on 28 november.
The company, according to Vaněk, decided to change the way to motivate its employees in exchange for overtime.
Either they receive the supplement for hours, or they can ask a replacement leave on 28 December and extend their Christmas and new year Aindiqué.
In addition to this all employees present on Saturday will receive compensation for the costs of transport and for their lunch.
Given the fact that overtime were the most urgent and most warm in the comments and the claims of the unions as employees who have voluntarily stopped production last week, management has taken the immediate decision to cancel all overtime for the month of December, said Vaněk.
Until last week, employees of the automotive plant were forced to work almost daily two overtime in addition to their eight hours.
The unions plan to cancel the state of strike after signing of the agreement.
The following negotiations between the management and unions to take place Friday afternoon.
The union leader Petr Kuchař said on Wednesday that they were ready to end the strike if agreement on their claims and signing of a common document.
The situation in the factory culminated last Wednesday when nearly 400 employees went on strike because of incessant overtime.
They were protesting against the poor pay and alleged bizutages.
Management has defended with the fact that employees had to work as a supplement to meet the requirements auto production.
At the announcement of the strike monday, the unions have also requested that the employees who have ceased production are not subject to any sanction.
The unions are asking the company to reduce the time spent in overtime to a minimum.
In addition, they want this year a reward of 5,000 crowns (209 €) for them.
The automotive plant Hyundai of Nošovice currently employs 2,000 people.
It started mass production last year in November.
It has produced approximately 80,000 vehicles until September of this year, with a production capacity of 200,000 cars per year.
Czech Discovery: a substance that operates on the HIV virus "resilient" also
A team of Czech and German scientists used to test new combinations that can slow the spread of the HIV virus in the body.
The main advantage of the substance improved is that it is also on the virus that have already developed an immunity to drugs.
This is, in some cases, the upper hand on the fact that the combination is not as hard on the common variants of the virus as well as some drugs already available.
It is not possible to cure AIDS.
It can prolong the life of patients through a mixture of drugs that prevent the spread of the HIV virus in the body.
Consumption, however, a series of side effects.
More repression of the development of so-called resistant viruses on which drugs have more effect.
The work of the experts of three institutions, the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic, the VŠCHT Prague and the University of Heidelberg paves the way for a way to cope with the resistance of the virus.
They have shown that substances called Metalocarboranes act on the protein responsible for the spread of the HIV virus.
The Metalocarboranes are an assembly of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
This combination is blocking the development of the virus in a different way of all drugs used to date and that is why they could overcome the problem of resistance.
The work of researchers leads them to discover new substances "improved", on the basis of their knowledge of the molecular mechanics of their routes on the proteins of the virus.
The Metalocarboranes have a single three-dimensional structure: two cages to multiple walls are formed by the boron atoms of hydrogen and carbon and connected by a metal atom, in this case the Cobalt.
A virus traitor and resilient. "
The HIV protease is a protein of the HIV virus which is essential to the life cycle of the virus.
Without the division of the HIV virus caused by the HIV protease inhibitor there would be no birth of mature infectious particles of the virus.
If you stop HIV protease, it will stop the spread of the virus in the body of the patient, the researchers explained in a press release issued by the Institute of Organic Chemistry and Biochemistry of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic.
In their work published in the scientific Journal Journal of Medicinal Chemistry, scientists describe a series of combinations where two pairs of cages (see table) are connected by a short organic link, which is then systematically amended.
A little smaller but more reliable.
The effectiveness of this series of substances on the HIV protease was tested in test tubes and its variants resistant, obtained from patients infected with HIV.
On the current version of the enzyme, the effect of metalocarboranes is not as strong as on the clinical medicine, but it has not weakened on resistant versions against which the current drugs are often ineffective.
The Metalocarboranes, with their unique mechanism of action and their other properties as their biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of other chemical changes are therefore interesting combinations to consider further move towards the development of effective drugs against HIV, says Pavlína Řezáčová, director of the structural biology laboratory of the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry and molecular genetics Institute of the Academy of Sciences.
