For two years, the only daughter of Liliane Bettencourt has committed criminal proceedings against François-Marie Banier, photographer and artist, which it accuses of having benefited for years from the weakness of his mother to obtain one billion euros in donations, in the form of cheques, contracts of life insurance or tables.
For its part, Liliane Bettencourt has always denied having been manipulated by the photographer, as an old friend.
While the court should examine the admissibility of the action taken by Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers, arguments from lawyers have sometimes turned into a large family unpacking Friday.
Thus, counsel Liliane Bettencourt reported three letters sent by his client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to his notary, in which she said beware of the husband of Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers.
In the letter dated 2003, Liliane Bettencourt added, according to the lawyer: "could you explain to my daughter that I wrote to Banier once, twice a day for 15 years.
Françoise, I have never been able to speak to him since his marriage ".
For its part, the prosecutor in Nanterre was again suggested that the complainant was not admissible to act, especially as a juvenile judge refused in recent days to grant his request to open a procedure of judicial protection for his mother.
Liliane Bettencourt "has full capacity to act, it is not under protection and has no guardian.
No one else has to act in his place, "said the representative of the public prosecutor, Marie-Chrsitine Daubigney.
The court has finally decided that it would decide once the trial will be held on the admissibility of Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers.
Managerial Revolution or end of the economic intelligence?
If nothing changes in the governance of large French companies, our struggle for the development of economic intelligence will have been in vain...
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies vis-à-vis its employees, said the companies' position vis-à-vis consumers before the revolution marketing: it is to join the staff to "values" determined from above as it was once, to impose on consumers of products designed by technicians of the plant.
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, the revolution has provided marketing strategies of conquest of markets where... although the authoritarian temptation to impose disconnected products to customers' preferences return regularly!
A demobilization of employees can lead to demoralization.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much more general phenomenon which affects.
This demobilization seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including R&D and, more importantly, the economic intelligence.
Indeed, the eis "requires of all stakeholders (...) a proactive approach and a forward-looking vision"; it requires a commitment that revenue management authoritarian bedevil completely.
That is why we call for a managerial revolution that would put the staff at the centre of the company in the same way as the client.
The usefulness of polls
The internal opinion surveys as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés- will encourage this revolution in the managerial practices?
Unfortunately, I am afraid not. "
- first because I saw that, faced with a new situation, any structure in the end, after many twists, priority … what it has always done.!
- Secondly, because authoritarianism - pathologies of pouvoir- increases in proportion to the importance of its own failures.
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behaviour.
From the major engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory behavioriste, cranked up recently by the "neuroscience" American and widely disseminated, without their knowledge, by the Institutes of studies and the media.
Thus, suggesting that it is possible to handle the "levers" (sic) the commitment of managers, a recent survey by Ipsos published in Le Figaro.fr conforte-t-elle leaders in a mechanistic governance posture, unsuited to today's world.
Identify and measure the factors of readiness
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, implies a finalist vision of human behaviour.
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental observation: For employees, the commitment to the company is possible only if it is clear as a means of achieving a part of their dreams, their ambitions, their projects.
Currently, only studies from the Analysis Motifonctionnelle adopt this design of employees.
These studies have shown that they consider their business based on a predetermined doxa which allows them through their image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life projects.
Thanks to the identification and the extent of these factors, business managers can control, and anticipate their "social" and their management of human resources "to".
They create a breeding ground for joint development of a robust and effective economic intelligence.
