Cleaning up university
Partial success for students: After a year of educational strike the Ministers of Education and Cultural Affairs of the Länder decide to be more conciliatory: at a meeting between Ministers and delegates from the Conference of Presidents, an agreement has been developed stipulating that the working conditions of students Bachelor or Master needed to be improved.
In the future, students should be able to overcome their studies.
They are particularly accordpour lighten the burden of reviews: a single review should close the module study.
In addition, the workload will be reconsidée proportions to ensure "realistic and acceptable".
The political authorities and institutions of higher education to facilitate the recognition of examinations between universities and abroad.
The Länder have also committed to organise common structural requirements more flexible for the Bachelor and Master.
At the regional level, there should not be any different from one land to another.
Less than reviews,
Since the beginning of the student protests last June, the Minister of Education of the Länder and the university rectors have repeatedly in the mouth the buzzword: "Étudiabilité."
But for the first time, this expression seems to take a practical meaning.
The accreditation council decided to significantly reduce the number of some reviews: "Each module should normally be concluded by a single consideration," reads a document of about 30 pages on future conditions of admission to the university cycles.
Reinhold Grimm, Chairman of the Board of Accreditation said that by sharply reducing the burden of reviews should be able to stop attacks, causing significant étudiabilité.
"Étudiabilité" should also be, in the future, the decisive criterion of the organization of studies.
The modules like the substance must be examined carefully to see if we cannot avoid this feeling of suffocation that we get in the choice of courses.
Hamburg / Berlin - According to the latest knowledge in RAID on Kunduz, the opposition believes that the Minister of defence Karl-Theodor zu Guttenberg (CSU) is guilty of deliberate deception.
Students should "have the opportunity and the flexibility to allow and encourage the personal initiative".
The new regulation will affect access to new university cycles but will also be adapted to the existing cycles.
These cycles must be "réaccrédités" every 5 years, which means, however, that it was not until 2015 that all cycles have been reviewed.
There are 10 relevant accreditation agencies throughout the federal territory which depend on the accreditation council created by the Länder.
In october, the Ministers of Education had exerted some pressure on the Länder to weigh on the agencies so that the programmes are not too busy and the regime of not too strict.
In some Länder, universities and colleges specialized have already agreed with their regional departments to take appropriate measures.
The Rhineland-Palatinate is so far the only Land to have agreed to grant more resources to the development of the Bologna process.
With these funds, universities must organize programs tutorielset strengthen the offices of educational guidance as well as the offices of reviews and the service of International Relations
The Länder and universities provide a budget of 10 million euros.
In early 2010, the government wants to submit to Parliament an amendment to the law on higher education institutions.
As a result, there will be no more one consideration to complete his studies.
The organization of studies should be more flexible, more must be able to guarantee the recognition of transcripts of other institutions of higher education and access to the Master must be simplified.
By the end of next year, the étudiabilité "of all university review.
Last thursday, the government and the opposition have again discussed the issue of conditions in the country.
The décisionsont been appreciated but there have been some criticisms.
The Federal President of the student union indicated that he would like the Organization of the education policy does not happen in the future "behind closed doors" of Ministers and rectors of universities.
After the strike, students as individuals should be able to speak a little.
The future of higher Education graduates received the support of the President of the delegates from the Conference of Presidents (HRK) Margret Wintermantel: "The experience of students is very useful," she said Thursday during a meeting with the Ministers of Education of the Länder with which the HRK is working on a project of reform.
For the union of Education and Science (GEW) decisions taken in Bonn do not go far enough. It calls for the right and the opportunity for each Bachelor degree to enroll in a cycle of Master.
Andreas Keller member of the steering committee of the GEW also asked that the Länder provide students Bachelor today, tomorrow there will be enough places for studies in Master and conditions of studies as good as possible.
The Länder must hire more lecturers.
However, the Ministers of Education have not raised the possibility of easing access to the Master.
More than a footnote on Herta Müller
It is by these words "Arrival in Germany and it is beautiful, almost more control..." that begins the poet Werner Söllner, in which he dealt with in snippets of sentences disturbing, the experiences of a dissident arrived in Germany who won freedom but has lost at the same time its linguistic territory.
Werner Söllner, born in 1951 to Banat in Romania, was first professor of German and English in Bucharest and, subsequently, director of collection in a publishing house for youth before moving to Frankfurt.
Söllner received various literary prizes; in 1993 he was the chair very popular poetry of the Goethe University in Frankfurt and since 2002 it is director of the Forum of Literature of Hesse to the house of artist of Mousonturm in Frankfurt.
He has done a lot of him in circles not literary last Tuesday, at a conference in Munich, whose theme was "The German literature in Romania in the mirror and the distorting mirror of your Securitate files".
Visibly upset and embarrassed, Söllner made a statement in which he acknowledged to his fellow writers Germano-roumains as Richard Wagner, William Totok, Franz Hodjak, and Helmuth Frauendorfer that he had worked as an informer for the Securitate political police.
Söllner received in 1989 the price of the German language together with some of the participants.
Tests began in 1971.
I am, "söllner so someone who has not sufficiently stood auxessais intimidation of the securitate."
The poet Werner Söllner is the informant Walter (MI Walter).
Almost simultaneously with the Honoration of the Nobel Prize for Herta Müller and his literary copies with the mechanisms of power of the dictatorship, the literary scene is shaken and in particular the community of German authors from Romania, in a case that clearly shows the abyss and of a political system based on police surveillance and espionage.
Werner Söllner is, as far as we can tell from the current knowledge, not only guilty but also victim.
In his own record Securitate, MI Walter played a role, ensures the specialist literature Michael Markel after the confession of Söllner and it refers to the positive influence of IM Walter, who had interceded on his behalf.
"He was able to draw all the difficult situations at the time," according to Markel.
Markel has felt the need to make this comment. moralde
The form in which Söllner made his statement and before the public was unexpected, however the admission of a former dissident its collaboration with the Romanian secret services is, in fact, not so surprising.
Germany is a reserve for the spies of the Securitate had already written Herta Müller in July in the newspaper Die Zeit, having read the 914 pages of his own record.
It can be assumed that the victims have made speculation and sometimes have guessed what real names were hiding last names borrowing Sorin, Voicu and Walter.
Unlike Germany, where the consultation of the Stasi files is a reliable process, the attitude to the legacy of the files of the Securitate is still very confused.
A systematic clarification has been repeatedly frustrated and slowed down in recent years.
It was only in 1999 that a national council corresponding to the institution Birthler was created to work on the assimilation of the archives of the Securitate (cnsas) but the transfer of files rather dragged since.
Since 2005, there is a law that defines the management of archives.
The influence of former members of the Securitate in Romania is still very great, is confirmed by an interview with a former head of the Securitate of Temesvar who, after the announcement of the award of the Nobel prize to Herta müller, spoke very dismissive of the winner.
She had a psychosis, and ultimately had questioned only once.
The infamy of power to speak here, without any gene, under the guise of freedom of expression.
Certainly, many issues are associated with the case Söllner as happens so often in a context of guilt.
Why now? Which has been deprived? The measured auditors, The admission of Söllner, gives us hope that The result of this chapter will be defined more by a thirst for knowledge that by accusations and a sense of shame.
On the genesis of the work of Herta müller, who received the Nobel prize, is more than a footnote.
