The promise of FonPeek
Peek is extremely limited, it is a device that allows only to watch his e-mail, without offering the possibility of even see some type of attachments or surf the Internet.
He took advantage of its five minutes of fame in the United States, when Time magazine designated as one of the products of the year.
In truth, it is more difficult to see in the street, but the idea seems interesting, especially for young people.
Unlike Smartphones, Peek offers a price and a monthly subscription very low, less than half of what it costs, for example, the subscription data of the iPhone.
Given its success, the company launched two new devices: one designed exclusively for Twitter, the other with a free service data to life, for six times more expensive than the Peek.
FonPeek, presented yesterday at The event The Web, is The European version of The invention and its third incarnation.
It is also limited by its large - American brother, but has a surprise.
The price of its monthly subscription, about 12 euros, includes the roaming across Europe.
Those who travel with a Smartphone already know what represents the fact renounce the data when it crosses a border or seek desperately a cafeteria on the Wifi (or a connection of Fon) to consult his mail.
The idea of a roaming at a fixed price is incredibly attractive and it is a long time that it should operate.
Indeed, some operators have special agreements and travel options, but as far as I am concerned, I would need to have a thesis in physics for the understanding and good glasses to read the small print.
Reminders of the European Commission to propose roaming fees affordable throughout Europe have had a barely perceptible.
Outside his country of origin, we hesitate to use the data, and it was not wrong.
A small device as the FonPeek (it is always curious that it is called Fon when it does not have the wifi) offers this type of tariffs, means that operators are starting to think differently and studying various proposals to make their data network.
Kindle is another good example, it includes downloading books and other research on the Internet.
Without subscription and.
It is a device connected and pay at its purchase and not every month.
And that is what I hope to see a day for the FonPeek: a purchase option with access to life as Peek proposes already in the United States.
Not that I want to buy it. "
I look at my mail on my phone, thank you. "
I would simply because I believe that it is a fairer formula for the consumer.
It would be interesting to see a computer with the same system.
The favourite colour of dr. Michelle
Yellow is, without doubt, the favourite colour of the First Lady of the United States.
If she went to the inauguration of Barack Obama to the presidency of the United States with a dress and a coat the color, she has chosen the same to accompany him in the second time, without doubt, the most important of his life: the surrender to Oslo for the Nobel Peace Prize.
Michelle Obama was a model very similar in these two occasions: in addition to their colour, a yellow drawing towards green with bright, both times, consisted of three parts: the dress, the jacket and mantle, in the same tissue, and was decorated with a large embroidery or a collar.
So that a first glance, it would appear that the first lady of the United States to follow the wake of Princess of Asturias and chose to return the same held.
But the fabric in which are cut both sets them very different.
If for the inauguration it was a thick lace, however, it was a printed velvet in Oslo.
The accessories also are different: green shoes to heel average for the first time, and a similar model, but, this time.
The also has changed: The hair are now identified when it was released last time.
75% of working mothers have had problems because of their maternity
Discrimination at work has increased in recent years, especially for women of younger generations who want to be mothers.
This study "Fertility and professional career women in Spain," conducted by the CSIC in collaboration with the Instituto de la Mujer.
The survey, conducted on 9 737 women aged 15 to 75 years, leaves no room for doubt: 75% of working mothers saw their professional career limited because of motherhood.
The study indicates that there are many differences concerning the beginning of life as a couple and the number of children, if the woman works or not and the job.
Those who do not work outside the home, working part-time or have a less stable, earlier couple, have their first pregnancy earlier and have more children.
In contrast, women with a stable job, mainly in the public sector, postpone the couple and the first pregnancy, and have fewer children.
Women aged between 35 and 49 with a fixed work have their first child, on average, 3.7 years after being installed as a couple. This figure rises to 4.1 among those working in the public sector. "These data show that women with a stable job needed more time in their lives for it, which led to push the union and the arrival of children.
In addition, the type of employment exercised influence largely motherhood, but less the start date of common life, "explains the researcher of the CSIC Margarita Delgado.
Education is another factor that widening the gap in the age of marriage for women and their first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of training, the more they marry and have their first child.
The difference is also among women of the same generation.
For example, in the group aged between 35 and 49 years, those who have elementary and higher were respectively mothers for the first time to 25.1 and 32.1 years on average.
"Another is also among women, according to their level of education.
While those who have done studies marry and have their first child before finding stable employment, those with a college or higher this programme and give priority to obtaining a stable work as a prerequisite to marriage and the arrival of a child, "said Mrs Delgado.
