Michelin and fesvial, sets for helmet-wearing
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the use of helmets, mainly among motorcyclists, like said today the two structures.
This initiative aims to raise awareness of the importance of helmets, since it is the only element of protection to avoid injuries to the head, or even death, in the event of an accident two wheels.
Michelin said that this campaign was in line with his commitment to road safety, which "goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer" and said she contributed to this objective by other actions to educational and informative.
This new campaign to encourage the helmet two wheels, under the motto "To be or not to be," will include a first phase during which posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages of motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination.
Finally, Michelin stressed that road safety "is a constant concern" for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products always safer.
The sale of light commercial vehicles is progressing
After nearly two years, the market for light commercial vehicles is beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9 425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the union of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, the dealers.
However, the good news, since the reference for comparison, the month of November 2008, has been particularly bad, with a 60% decrease compared to the previous year.
As a result, despite the rebound last month, registrations accumulated during the 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, if you add up all the vehicles which fall into the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, pickup trucks, vans, and light trucks lightweight chassis) 95,853 were sold.
Large clouds that most affect their application have not dissipated. Indeed, although they are also purchased by individuals, most purchases are made by small and medium-sized companies, which pay in almost 100% of cases through external funding.
Thus, in addition to the restrictions involved by restricting bank loans, other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the downturn.
Faced with this situation and unlike cars, aid to the purchase of the 2000E have little used.
In addition to individuals, the self-employed and SMEs wishing to acquire a light commercial vehicle of less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of Co2 emissions that does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, can also benefit, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
Yesterday, in ganvam, recalled the need for the administration to pay particular attention to these vehicles and industrial vehicles (trucks and buses).
The dealers association provides a year 2010 similar to that end, for which it calculates a drop in sales (for passenger cars and 4 x 4) of 19%.
The emergency braking is now mandatory
As has occurred with the ABS anti-lock system and as it will take place with the ESP stability control systems to help emergency braking will be a compulsory element on European cars.
They are already mandatory on passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while for the rest of the vehicles a waiting period has been set until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen the protection of pedestrians, even if, by its mode of action, it can also help prevent many rear shocks.
The assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system through the kick given by the driver.
But it does not always maintained the pressure until the end. "
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars bosch, a third of drivers involved in an accident had not been able to slam on the brakes before the collision, and half of them had not benefited from strength.
Up to 1,100
The intervention of the aid, Revancha, requires the maximum brake system, reducing the distance that the car needs to stop.
According to a study of the eu, if all cars were equipped with such elements, up to 1,100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
This reduction would be even more important with the popularization of so-called intelligent emergency braking systems: It calculates that a disaster on four with casualties would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system which, thanks to a radar or a camera, detects obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, it means increasing the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device the maximum effort on the brakes in order to minimize the damage.
