Sra. Rushmore is adjudiquer advertising of Renfe
Renfe has entrusted the services of advertising and marketing of these two years to the agency sra. rushmore, for a budget of about three million euros per year, said the rail operator.
The contract mentions the possibility of two extensions of 12 months each. sra. Rushmore was chosen from among 16 agencies that completed the tender organised by renfe, of which four were finalists, including TBWA who was responsible for creativity during the last three years.
From now on, Sra. Rushmore will be responsible for the design and production of campaigns.
A fine of 63 million to France Telecom to curb competition.
The French competition regulator imposed a fine of 63 million euros to France Telecom for its anti-competitive conduct in the Caribbean region belonging to the country.
According to this institution, the operator has limited competition in the fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements, tariffs and loyalty programs to consumers in the margins of the regulation.
With this sanction, the former French monopoly and even state company, accumulates over 450 million euros in fines since 1994, because of the obstacles it puts its competitors.
The sanction imposed yesterday has been increased because the authority which ensures competition considers that France Telecom has committed similar offences in the past and that it is therefore.
A shop applications.
On the other hand, the mobile phone subsidiary of the French company has followed the wake of other operators and opened a shop of Internet applications, with the objective of increasing revenue from outside the transmission of voice.
Initially, the store applications of Orange will be active in France and the United Kingdom.
Until 2010 to arrive in other countries such as Spain.
Their participation in the Champions League reported 476,4 million to Real Madrid and since its creation
The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992.
Indeed, Real Madrid and FC Barcelona have won 467,4 million, which puts them in the third and fifth position of clubs who have pocketed the most money in this competition.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
Win the UEFA Champions League does not only the glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of big clubs.
Indeed, the competition has allocated 5 362,5 million euros to 105 teams (including 12 Spanish) who participated in the event since the creation of the tournament, during the 1992-93 season, according to information from UEFA.
Real Madrid and FC Barcelona have been well served in this division.
The club was the third of the continent to receive the most money for his participation, and the only one, with the A.C. Milan, has won three times the trophy.
The Catalan club, taking the title and last winner of the old European Cup in 1992, is fifth on the list.
At the top of the list are the Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams, billed the more money for their participation in the last Champions League.
And that, although they lost in the +36.
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, in the money reported by the Champions League, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while Italy has won four, England three and Germany two).
He divides
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of distribution of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini expects to earn $1 million through the Champions League.
Of this amount, UEFA will spend 413.1 million fixed payments: Each of the 20 clubs who participated in the classification matches (including the Atlético Madrid) received 2.1 million.
In addition, those who have managed to participate received 3.8 million just to be there, more than 550 00 euros for each match.
There is also a bonus in case of victory (800,000 euros) and equality (400 000 for each team). Those who arrive in eighth finals receive three million each, the eight teams who arrive in the final quarter of reçoivent3,3 million.
The last four teams will each receive.
And the champion will win $9 million, the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will earn at least 7.1 million, and a maximum 31.2 million.
On the other hand, the Barça pocketed $2.5 million for winning the Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are the payments, which are 337,8 million.
This money is distributed according to the value of each market.
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four places.
The champion of the previous year gets 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other party will be paid according to the number of matches played during the edition of the year.
Nueva Rumasa offer 61 million euros to 29.9 per cent of Sos.
The group Nueva Rumasa listed yesterday the details of the offer to purchase of shares by which it intends to acquire a maximum of 25 to 29.9% of the capital of Sos.
A percentage which did not require him to launch a takeover bid (OPA) for all of the securities.
Specifically, Nueva Rumasa offers 1,5025 euros per share, which will be disbursed over 10 years and will be paid at a rate of 1% per year for the postponement.
Yesterday, the shares of Sos have completed 1.85 euros; the supply of Nueva Rumasa therefore assesses the company 18% below the market.
According to Nueva Rumasa, the price of 1.50 euros reflects the real assessment of Sos.
The offer is conditioned by the appointment of eight of the 15 advisers.
The group of Jerez gives a period of 15 days for shareholders to indicate their interest in the sale of securities.
The CNMV assured not having been informed of this offer, although the company of Ruiz Mateos has said that it had made contact with the regulator.
If he had, the disbursement would 611,7 million, while capital of Sos is 254,27 million.
In the meantime, Sos continues the restructuring of its direction.
In an attempt to remain outside any bids and the coming and going of its former directors, brothers Jesús and Jaime Salazar, it announced the election of María Luis Jordá as Director of Internal Audit.
A decision that in fact the first woman to hold a post leader in the company.
It is a newly created position that will depend directly to the president of the group.
And it is not without controversy, as the company remains submerged in the legal battle for the alleged embezzlement of more than 230 million Sos to companies of Salazar.
Moreover, the possibility that in the coming months Sos reveals new misappropriation of funds cannot be ruled out.
On the credit to salazar, the former advisers Ildefonso Ortega and Ángel Fernández Noriega (representatives of the CCM and unicaja) said yesterday before the National Audience that they had been informed of the diversion of 212 million without knowing the destination.
The CNMV allows the exclusion presented by sea
The National Commission of the securities market (CNMV) allowed yesterday the Opt-Out takeover bid filed by Inversora Sea on Federico Paternina on 9 October last year.
The oversight body explained that he authorized this operation because he understood that his words reflected the standards in force and that he considered "adequate" the content of the explanatory sheet submitted, following the changes implemented on 2 December last year.
The CNMV said that the offer for the acquisition of 550 008 actions of Federico Paternina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, which is 8.95% of the capital, consisting of 6 142 786 shares admitted to trading on the stock exchanges in Madrid and Bilbao.
He also explained that 5 592 778 million shares were immobilized, and that they could not in any way be transmitted before the finalisation of the offer, which he said that the price was set by Federico Paternina, in accordance with the provisions of existing standards.
New tools for the expertise of our cars
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are reduced to a garage, where an expert to assess the damage and the cost of the repair.
Every disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of the parts and labor can be a long and complex process.
To calculate the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and labour can take two or three hours.
However, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
It is for this reason that almost 100% of experts use such systems.
Suppliers of services and solutions for the assessment of claims and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by manufacturers, and then treat them and offer their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, Solera North American group, is the company leader; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies in competition in the field of evaluation tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each provides information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to address continues to increase, so that in the past five years, more than versions, and have been launched in the last 15 years.
When a new car lots on the market, these companies are at work.
It is a very difficult, because each thousand pieces of the vehicle and put its price.
In addition, it establishes a graphic image "smart" of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a passenger vehicle.
If it is a model sold heavily, the work can be ready in a week if the process moving very quickly.
If it is a little car sold, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex provides complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, for example, they have on the porsche, but not the Ferrari or lamborghini.
On vehicles in circulation, the figure is over 99 per cent.
To documentation and development of databases, Audatex has eight centres throughout the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid). "
Here, more than 100 technicians (usually experts in mechanical) work simultaneously on three screens of computers.
Audatex invests each year, 90 million to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and clients receive updates every two days.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and products.
The most common application for the repair and maintenance, but in different countries, there are also tools for the management of pieces of breaks or to calculate the residual value or a car.
The only company that has a guide on the value of used cars in Spain is eurotax.
Audatex does not propose in our country, but it does in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard assessment of claims, for experts.
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it takes into account the time repair estimated by the manufacturer or the scales of paint.
This tool is bought in terms of its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use little, up to 10 times a month.
Then, each insurance company, which conducts thousands of expertise, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the identification of a vehicle and equipment with which he came out of the assembly line, only through its chassis number.
Audaglass focuses on the glasses of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is open to the professional sector server on the Internet to bid on vehicles reported wrecks.
Its statistical service is very useful for identifying trends, analyses géo-démographiques or know the current problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a mark went to the garage for a breakdown or how many have suffered serious losses for a given period.
GT Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It sells, among others, Gt Estimate, which is also intended to experts and provides digital images, as well as access to official documents, price and time of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the group Einsa, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of claims, breakdowns or maintenance devoiture.
The guide GT assessment is a historical reference product on the market.
The company works with 24,000 users in garages, 3 100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its business volume has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the past three years, and it has a turnover of EUR 10.8 million in 2008.
At the beginning of last year, she began the process of internationalization, with the establishment of an office in Paris.
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and is located in Spain in 1979.
According to the sources of the company, 62% of its turnover is done in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38 per cent in North and South America. It works with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 garages, including 3,000 are in Spain.
The global turnover of the group Solera (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will amount to $557 million, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company will collect 19.1 million euros, or 7.2 per cent more than last year.
In 2005, the group Solera was traded 1 000 million, today, its shares are valued at a total of 2,400 million.
Since 2007, it is part of the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the benchmark Standard & Poor's.
Internet auction of rugged
Last October, the group has purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles.
The operation has involved a cost of 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could grow next year to 15 per cent.
The purpose of the acquisition was to provide more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This service and sales is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, garages, breaks and sellers professionals who must be registered before starting to carry out operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Among its major markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 sellers and 4,000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3,000 announcements by day and on the Spanish market, 100 new announcements are published every day.
Under Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been withdrawn can no longer move, but on the other hand, some parts which are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
The vintage cars can be réenregistrées, although they have been withdrawn, after complex.
In four stages
With the tool Auda-Taller, the company Audatex ensures that the user gets a quotation in only four steps: identify the vehicle, seek the replacement, create a quotation and generate.
The ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince the oldest professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1 034 vehicles, including 666 Tourism, 109, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and trucks.
Of course, to use a computer and an Internet connection.
Once the model to repair identified through its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question is then selects the necessary.
The user can include variables such as the price of labour, increases or reductions, then it can print the specifications for the client.
Audataller is not a tool to estimate as AudaPlus, but a catalogue of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that for garages does not include the time of Labour estimated.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which may be the subject of a credit.
Currently, the company Audatex works for that these images are in three dimensions.
It is an innovation that mechanics are a very good eye, as it will, for example, to select a door and turn to see the inside.
